<Issue id="40485" key="FAB-15664" number="15664" project="10002" reporter="ales" creator="ales" type="10004" summary="LSCC: nil ChaincodeSpec in LSCC DEPLOY/UPGRADE args causes peers to crash" priority="3" resolution="10002" status="6" created="2019-06-09 07:47:16.0" updated="2019-08-07 19:46:22.0" resolutiondate="2019-08-07 19:43:56.0" votes="0" watches="12" workflowId="53420" security="10000"> <description><! CDATA h1. Problem  An LSCC DEPLOY/UPGRADE transaction contains marshalled ChaincodeDeploymentSpec as part of the chaincode arguments. If the ChaincodeSpec field is nil, committing peers will crash because of the nil pointer dererference. They will enter a crash/restart loop after that.  This has security implications because it amounts to a DoS  ></description> </Issue>
